arts.ttl: Collins caps five-star Brentford’s Carabao Cup cruise against Grimsby
arts.sum: Brentford sauntered into the League Cup quarter-finals for the second consecutive season after ending Grimsby’s magnificent cup run on a one-sided evening in Cleethorpes. The Mariners had beaten teams from each of England’s top three divisions to reach the fourth round, including their historic win against Manchester United at this ground in August. However, there was never really any chance of a repeat here as Keith Andrews’s team continued their fine recent form to silence a sold-out Blundell Park. Continue reading...

arts.ttl: Nelson stars for five-star Brentford in Grimsby thrashing
arts.sum: Reiss Nelson starred on his first Brentford start as the Bees strolled into the Carabao Cup quarter-finals with a dominant 5-0 win to end League Two Grimsby Town's memorable run in the competition.

arts.ttl: Carvalho and Nelson start for Brentford vs Grimsby LIVE on Sky!
arts.sum: In their way is another Premier League opposition in Brentford - who have treated the League Cup very seriously in recent years. In the last five years they have three quarter-final appearances and one semi-final spot in this competition.

arts.ttl: Keith Andrews affirms his respect for Grimsby Town
arts.sum: The team are flying high off the back of a 3-2 win against reigning Premier League champions Liverpool at the Gtech Community Stadium, and a tally of 13 points has put the players eight clear of the relegation zone. Andrews wants to keep the momentum from the weekend rolling onwards, and that will only be possible with maximum respect for the opposition.
